headlines.description: Relegation-battling Lecce halted Napoli's revival with a shock 3-2 win at the Stadio San Paolo on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Napoli's winning run ends with shock loss to Lecce

headlines.description: Lazio moved one point behind Serie A leaders Juventus with a 1-0 win at Parma, setting a new club record of 18 consecutive unbeaten league games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lazio beat Parma to close Serie A gap on Juve

headlines.description: Inter Milan went top of Serie A on Sunday after completing a remarkable second half comeback to overturn a two-goal deficit and beat AC Milan 4-2.
headlines.shortLinkText: Inter go top of Serie A after wild Milan derby win
